Comcast to Buy Blackstone’s Stake in Parks, TheWrap.com Reports

-- B y   A n t h o n y   P a l a z z o
-- 
2011-05-31T05:07:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/comcast-to-buy-blackstone-s-stake-in-parks-thewrap-com-reports.html
Comcast Corp. (CMCSA) , owner of NBC Universal
Inc., intends to acquire Blackstone Group’s 50 percent stake in
two Universal theme parks in  Florida , the website TheWrap.com
reported.  Comcast is expected to pay $1 billion to $1.5 billion for
the stake in Universal Studios Florida and Islands of Adventure,
the website said, citing a person with knowledge of the deal.
Comcast’s board is expected to approve the transaction, the
website said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Palazzo in Los Angeles at 
